    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about needing an escrow account for this house i'm looking at in toronto. i've never bought a place before so i'm kinda lost. can u explain what escrow actually is and why it's even used in the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure, I'd be happy to help! An escrow account is a special account where funds are held by a neutral third party, known as an escrow agent, until all conditions of the real estate purchase are met. The main purpose is to ensure that both the buyer and seller meet their obligations, like paying the down payment and securing financing, before transferring the property. This helps protect both parties and ensures a smooth closing process. Remember, the escrow agent is not a party to the transaction but acts as a trusted intermediary to ensure that all parties fulfill their commitments.",
