      "content": "Good question! In the event of a mistake or delay, the Escrow Agent has procedures in place to handle such situations. They may work with all parties involved, including attorneys and lenders, to resolve the issue and ensure that the funds are released appropriately. If a delay occurs, it doesn't mean the money sits indefinitely. Escrow Agents and the involved parties strive to communicate and resolve any issues promptly. However, it's important to note that some delays can cause additional costs or fees, depending on the circumstances. It's always best to work closely with your real estate professionals, such as your lawyer and realtor, to clarify any concerns or questions about the escrow process and how to address potential hiccups.",
